tional  funding.  I  think  the  flat-line  trend  puts  us  further  behind
the  eight  ball,  and  it  is  my  opinion  that  the  results,  the  economic
return,  on  the  aeronautic  side,  is  equal  to  that  of  the  space  side.
Could  we  count  on  you  to  push  for—within  the  context  of  your  re-
sponsibilities,  additional  funding,  at  least  to  keep  pace  with  infla-
tion?

Dr. GRIFFIN. Sir, my first priority will be to effectively—to utilize
effectively the money that we are given. I will be working with this
committee and other executive agencies to do that.

Mr. UDALL. Let me turn—and I think this conversation will con-

tinue, if I might conclude in that way——

Dr. GRIFFIN. Sure.
Mr.  UDALL.—because  I  do  think  the  aeronautics  side  is  crucial

